# 🪑 EmptyCup Interior Designer Listing – Full Stack Assignment

A mobile-responsive frontend + Flask backend application that lists interior designers with shortlist functionality. Built for the EmptyCup Full Stack assignment using HTML/CSS/JS and Python (Flask).

---

## 📁 Folder Structure

```plaintext
emptycup-assignment/
├── backend/
│   ├── app.py              
│   └── designers.json     
└── frontend/
    ├── index.html          
    ├── styles.css          
    ├── script.js          
              
Make sure you have Python installed (3.7+ recommended).

Open a terminal in VS Code.

Navigate to the backend folder:

cd backend
Install required packages:

pip install flask flask-cors
Start the Flask backend server:

python app.py
✅ The backend will run at: http://127.0.0.1:5000
📡 API Endpoint available: GET /api/designers

🌐 Frontend Setup
Open VS Code and navigate to the frontend/ folder.

Open index.html in a browser:

You can right-click > Open with Live Server (if using VS Code Live Server extension)

Or manually open it from your file system in a browser.

⚠️ Important: Ensure the backend is already running before loading the frontend so that designer data loads correctly via the API.


🖼️ UI Overview
🧾 Designer Cards Display
Each card shows:

🏷️ Name

⭐ Rating

📦 Projects completed

📅 Years of experience

💰 Price range

📞 Two contact numbers

🛠️ Actions on Each Card
🔍 Details – More info (currently non-functional)

🙈 Hide – (optional logic placeholder)

❤️ Shortlist / Unshortlist – Add/remove from shortlist

🚩 Report – Placeholder

📄 Filter Options (Top Navbar)
📋 All

🖼️ Gallery

🗺️ Map

❤️ Shortlisted – Toggle to view only shortlisted designers

💡 Features
✅ Dynamic data fetch from Flask backend

✅ Shortlist logic using JavaScript Set


🚀 Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML, CSS, Vanilla JavaScript

Backend: Python (Flask), Flask-CORS

Data Source: Static JSON file (designers.json)


🧪 Testing the App
Run the backend (python app.py)

Open the frontend (index.html)

Click Shortlist, toggle Shortlisted view

Ensure designer data appears correctly